         <abstract>
            <p>Let $T_k(n)$ denote the number of solutions in nonnegative integers $a_i$, of the equation $$n = \sum^k_{i=1} \sum^{k-i+1}_{j=1} a_{ij}$$ where the $a_{ij}$ satisfy the inequalities $a_{ij} \geqslant a_{i+1,j}, a_{ij} \geqslant a_{i+1,j-1}$. We show that $$\sum^\infty_{n=1} T_k(n)x^n = (1 - x)^{-k}(1 - x^3)^{-k+1}(1 - x^5)^{-k+2} \cdots (1 - x^{2k-1})^{-1}.$$</p>
          </abstract>
